article.description: Reggie Baker scored 20 points on 6-for-11 shooting from 3 point range, Diamante Lewis just missed a triple-double, and Bethune Cookman -- which knocked down 12 3s -- beat Florida A&M 69-59 on Thu
article.headline: Bethune-Cookman downs Florida A&M 69-59 behind parade of 3s
article.linkText: Bethune-Cookman downs Florida A&M 69-59 behind parade of 3s
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. -- Reggie Baker scored 20 points on 6-for-11 shooting from 3 point range, Diamante Lewis just missed a triple-double, and Bethune Cookman -- which knocked down 12 3s -- beat Florida A&M 69-59 on Thursday night. Bethune Cookman (9-21, 6-10 Mid-Eastern Athletic) finished 12 for 29 from 3-point range. The Wildcats started with an 18-7 run with the help of four 3-pointers and never trailed. The Wildcats led 37-24 at halftime shooting 15 for 30, including 7 for 18 from 3-point range. Five different Wildcats connected from 3 before the break. Meanwhile, Florida A&M (7-22, 5-11) shot 9 for 35, including 2 for 12 from 3. Lewis finished with 10 rebounds, 10 assists and nine points, Brandon Tabb scored 12 points and Quinton Forrest had 10 points on 5-for-6 shooting. Baker also grabbed nine boards. Desmond Williams led Florida A&M (7-22, 5-11) with 18 points and Marcus Barham added 13.
